title: Southampton vs Leicester City - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 8
description: Having done the double over Leicester in their last Premier League campaign together of 2022-23, Southampton lost both Championship meetings with the Foxes last term by an aggregate score of 9-1. Leicester are winless in their last three Premier League away games against Southampton since a 9-0 win under Brendan Rodgers in October 2019.

title: Sevilla vs Valencia - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 19
description: After four consecutive wins over Valencia in LaLiga between 2020 and 2021, Sevilla have won just one of their last five games against them in the competition. Sevilla have not won either of their last two LaLiga home games against Valencia and have not gone 3+ without a home win over Valencia in the top-flight since a run of 11 between 1992 and 2005.

title: Mallorca vs Barcelona - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 19
description: Mallorca have lost 14 and drawn just two of their last 16 meetings vs FC Barcelona in LaLiga, the worst winless run against the same opponent in their entire history in the top-flight. Their last league win against FC Barcelona was in May 2009 on the antepenultimate matchday. FC Barcelona have won 81% of their away games against Mallorca in the 21st Century, their highest percentage of away wins against the same opponent in the competition in at least 10 meetings since then.

title: Athletic Bilbao vs Real Madrid - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 19
description: Athletic Club have not won any of their last 18 matches against Real Madrid in LaLiga, since a 1-0 win in March 2015 with current coaches Ernesto Valverde and Carlo Ancelotti on the respective benches, their worst winless run against the same opponent in the competition ever. Real Madrid have collected points in their last nine visits to Athletic Club in LaLiga, winning the last five. No team in the history of the competition has ever won six straight away victories against the Basque side.

title: Espanyol vs Leganes - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 19
description: This will be the ninth meeting between Espanyol and Leganes in LaLiga, with each side having won both meetings in the season each time: Espanyol in 16/17 and 18/19 and Leganes in 17/18 and 19/20. CD Leganes have won three of their last five away games against Espanyol in all competitions, having lost in the three previous meetings. All three wins at Espanyols home ground have been by the same scoreline: 1-0.

title: Deportivo Alaves vs Girona - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 19
description: Alaves have won two, drawn two and lost two of their six matches against Girona in LaLiga, repeating the same pattern: win - loss - draw. In their last meeting, the two sides played out a 2-2 draw in Vitoria last May. After winning six of their first seven home games against Girona in all competitions, Alaves have won just two of their next seven at home against the Catalans.

title: Atletico Madrid vs Osasuna - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 19
description: Atletico de Madrid lost their last match against Osasuna in LaLiga, 1-4 last May, having won each of their previous 11 against the Navarrese side in the competition, and have not lost 2+ in a row against them in the top-flight since October 2009 under Abel Resino. Osasuna won 4-1 on their last visit to Atletico de Madrid in LaLiga and have only twice in their history collected points in two consecutive away games against the red-and-whites in the competition.

title: Sevilla vs Valencia - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 19
description: After four consecutive wins over Valencia in LaLiga between 2020 and 2021, Sevilla have won just one of their last five games against them in the competition. Sevilla have not won either of their last two LaLiga home games against Valencia and have not gone 3+ without a home win over Valencia in the top-flight since a run of 11 between 1992 and 2005.

title: Real Betis vs Deportivo Alaves - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 20
description: Real Betis have not lost any of their last seven meetings with Alaves in LaLiga, drawing the last three. These two sides have never drawn 4+ games in a row against one another in the top-flight. Alaves have collected points in three of their last five away games against Real Betis in LaLiga, as many times as they managed in their first eight such visits in the competition.

title: Real Madrid vs Las Palmas - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 20
description: Real Madrid have not lost any of their 35 home games against UD Las Palmas in LaLiga, a record number of home matches without defeat by any team against an opponent in the history of the competition. Following the 1-1 draw in the reserve fixture this season, UD Las Palmas have the chance to collect points in their two matches against Real Madrid in the same LaLiga season for the fourth time in history, having previously achieved this in the 1966/67, 1978/79 and 2016/17 campaigns.

title: Valencia vs Real Sociedad - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 20
description: Valencia have lost their last three meetings with Real Sociedad in LaLiga, failing to score in all three, equalling their worst run of consecutive defeats without scoring against the San Sebastian side in the competition. Real Sociedad have lost just three of their last 13 away games against Valencia in LaLiga, having lost in eight of their previous 11 such games in the competition.

title: Getafe vs Barcelona - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 20
description: Getafe have not lost any of their last four games at the Coliseum against Barcelona in LaLiga, keeping clean sheets in all four, their best home run both unbeaten and without conceding against the Azulgrana side in the competition. Barcelona have drawn against Getafe in their last three visits to the Coliseum in LaLiga, all three by the same scoreline. Never in their entire history in the competition have the Blaugranas had four consecutive 0-0 draws away from home against an opponent.

title: Girona vs Sevilla - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 20
description: Girona have won their last six games against Sevilla in LaLiga, their best run of consecutive victories against the same opponent in their top-flight career. Sevilla are also the team against whom the Catalan side have won most often against in the competition. After winning on their first visit to Montilivi in LaLiga, Sevilla have lost their last three away games against Girona. No other away team have lost more matches against the Catalan side in the top-flight.

title: Villarreal vs Mallorca - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 20
description: Villarreal have not won either of their last two home games against Mallorca in LaLiga, having never gone three home games in a row without a win against them in the competition. Mallorca have won two of their last five games against Villarreal in LaLiga, managing just one win fewer than in their previous 21 matches in the competition.

title: Lille vs Monaco - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 23
description: Lille have lost 14 times at home against ASM in Ligue 1, more often than against any other opponent in the top-flight. However, Losc have now won two games in a row at home against Monaco and could make it three in a row for the first time since 2009-2013. Lille have 38 points this season in Ligue 1, exactly as many after 22 games as in the previous two seasons. Their record of 10 wins, eight draws and four losses is in fact the same as in 2023-24, though Losc did then lose their 23rd game.

title: Auxerre vs Olympique Marseille - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 23
description: Winners at the Velodrome on November 8, Auxerre could win home and away against Marseille in the same Ligue 1 season for the second time in their history, after 1987-88. Auxerre have picked up 15 more points at home than away this season in Ligue 1, the joint-biggest difference along with Rennes. Meanwhile, Marseille are the team with the largest such differential away from home.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 23
description: Lyon have lost three consecutive games against Paris SG in Ligue 1 and could suffer four defeats in a row against PSG in the top-flight for the second time in their history, after September 1981-April 1983. Since the arrival of QSI in 2011/12, Lyon have won four times at home against Paris SG in Ligue 1, no team has won more on home soil against PSG over that period.

title: Saint-Étienne vs Angers SCO - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 23
description: ● St Etienne have lost just two of their last 28 games in all competitions against Angers, but one of those two losses came in the reverse fixture this season in Ligue 1. ASSE conceded twice as many goals in that game as in their previous six in all competitions against SCO. St Etienne are unbeaten in their last 17 home games against Angers in all competitions, their longest unbeaten home record against a team currently in Ligue 1.

title: Nantes vs Lens - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 23
description: Nantes have lost each of their last four Ligue 1 games against Lens, their longest current run against an opponent in the top-flight. Nantes have won 27 Ligue 1 home games against Lens, their joint-most against any side. Beaten 0-1 last season, FCN could, however, suffer two consecutive losses at La Beaujoire against RCL for the first time since 1999-2001.

title: Nice vs Montpellier - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 23
description: Nice have won six of their last eight Ligue 1 home games against Montpellier. However, OGCN have lost two of the last three L1 home games against MHSC, including the one last season. title: Lens vs Le Havre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 24
description: Lens have won just two of their last 16 games against Le Havre in all competitions, but won the most recent one on 12 January.
